'Cangjie programming language_class_subtype_subtype_class_inheritance': 'In Cangjie code language, When a class inherits from another class, the subclass becomes a subtype of the superclass. This means that an instance of the subclass can be used wherever an instance of the superclass is expected.'

Code_Example:
open class Super { }
class Sub <: Super { }

'Cangjie programming language_class_subtype_subtype_interface_implementation': 'In Cangjie code language, When a type implements an interface, it becomes a subtype of that interface. This means that an instance of the implementing type can be used wherever an instance of the interface is expected.'

Code_Example:
interface I1 { }
interface I2 { }
interface I3 <: I1 & I2 { }
class C <: I1 { }
extend Int64 <: I2 { }

Error_case_code:
// file1.cj
package p1

public class A{}
public func get(): Any {
    return A()
}
//

'Cangjie programming language_class_subtype_subtype_tuple_types': 'In Cangjie code language, In Cangjie, a tuple type (T1, T2, ..., TN) is a subtype of another tuple type (U1, U2, ..., UN) if each element type Ti is a subtype of the corresponding element type Ui.'

Code_Example:
open class C1 { }
class C2 <: C1 { }

open class C3 { }
class C4 <: C3 { }

let t1: (C1, C3) = (C2(), C4()) // OK
let t2: (C3, C1) = (C4(), C2()) // OK

'Cangjie programming language_class_subtype_subtype_function_types': 'In Cangjie code language, In Cangjie, a function type (U1) -> S2 is a subtype of another function type (U2) -> S1 if U2 is a subtype of U1 and S2 is a subtype of S1.'

Code_Example:
open class U1 { }
class U2 <: U1 { }
open class S1 { }
class S2 <: S1 { }

func f(a: U1): S2 { S2() }
func g(a: U2): S1 { S1() }
func call1() {
    g(U2()) // Ok.
    f(U2()) // Ok.
}
func h(lam: (U2) -> S1): S1 {
    lam(U2())
}
func call2() {
    h(g) // Ok.
    h(f) // Ok.
}

'Cangjie programming language_class_subtype_subtype_transitivity': 'In Cangjie code language, Subtype relationships in Cangjie are transitive. If A <: B and B <: C, then A <: C.'

Code_Example:
interface I1 { }
interface I2 <: I1 { }
class C <: I2 { }
extend Bool <: I2 { }
